snippet.textDisplay:
As a dog trainer of 20+ years experience, I found Marbles’ learning process fascinating! He really did do well. Dogs are a lot smarter than we often give them credit for. A lot of their lives are spent trying to communicate with us stoopid hoomans through body language, which mostly goes completely ignored.

Eleven isn’t old for a chihuahua-some have been known to live for over 20 years! My own chihuahua-sized Sheltie (9 pounds at his heaviest) lived to be 18 years old. He was learning tricks the month before his death!
